The parameterization review is complete and confirms a P0 mismatch: the sketch collapses central knowledge, projection, and strategic credit into one `G`, even though the existing gate separates noisy value estimation from the credit-weighted ranking decision. It also omits load-bearing arguments such as `λ`, `h`, costs, budget share, reach, and the world generator, so the advertised “small θ” currently hides fixed assumptions rather than governing the full surface.
