104:for(const cap of [0,0.2,0.5]) console.log("   capture="+cap.toFixed(1)+": advantage "+(cap===0?medAdv(0,0.25):medAdvCap(0,0.25,cap)).toFixed(2)+"x");

--- analytic key lines ---
1:#!/usr/bin/env node
2:// E4 ANALYTICAL BACKBONE — proves the three closed forms the simulations obey, and
3:// verifies each against the simulation output. Converts "sim seeking a headline"
4:// into "theorem confirmed by simulation".
5://
6:// PROP 1 (parity law).  Both institutions estimate the same Samuelson value of a
7://   project, T = S+ - S-, where S+ = sum of positive valuations, S- = sum of |negative|.
8://   Each ranks projects by a harm-discounted estimate T_hat = S+ - theta * S-.
9://     central keeps gamma of perceived harm      -> theta_C = gamma
10://     distributed: harmed participate at (1-beta) -> theta_D = 1 - beta   (global p cancels)
11://   True harm weight is 1. Whichever theta is closer to 1 ranks closer to truth, so
12://   DISTRIBUTED DOMINATES iff |1-theta_D| < |1-theta_C|  <=>  beta < 1 - gamma.
13://   Parity locus: beta* = 1 - gamma (anti-diagonal). Verified against the v4 frontier.
14://
15:// PROP 2 (capture threshold).  From Becker rent > acquisition + P(detect)*penalty:
16://     lambda*_central     = (k_c + p_c*F) / C
17://     lambda*_distributed = k_d + p_d*F / C
18://     resistance ratio     rho(C) = (k_d*C + p_d*F) / (k_c + p_c*F), rising in C,
19://   with an irreducible distributed floor k_d (equal-wallet acquisition scaling).
20://
21:// PROP 3 (detection floor).  p = 1 - (1-q)^m  =>  m*q = -ln(1-p). Only the product
22://   m*q matters; beating a central rate p_c needs m*q >= -ln(1-p_c).
